"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-04-paris-2024-olympics-im-proud-of-my-girls-wakama-reacts-to-dtigress-win-over-canada\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  D'Tigress head coach Rena Wakama was full of excitement after her side sealed a place in the quarter-finals of the women's basketball event at the 2024 Olympic Games.  The African champions outclassed the world number five Canada 79-70 in their last group game.  Wakama's side won two and lost one of their three group games.  D'Tigress made history as the first African team to claim a place in the quarter-finals in the history of the Olympics.  \\\"It's surreal and I do not think it's going to hit me yet for another couple of hours,\\\" Wakama told FIBA.com.  \\\"I am proud of my girls and I have pushed them so hard. I have pushed them harder than anyone can even imagine. It's because I know what they can do and we did that today and we showed them who we are.\\\"  Paris 2024 Olympics: Ajayi, Ashe disappoint in men's 100m semis  Transfer: Not about money - Chelsea striker Guiu on leaving Barcelona  D'Tigress maintain 8th position in latest FIBA women's rankings  FIBA WWCQ: D'Tigress star Macaulay named in All-Star team  D'Tigress captain Ogoke retires from national team  FG fulfils pledge to D'Tigress for winning 2025 FIBA Women's Afrobasket  2026 FIBA World Cup Qualifiers: D'Tigress rally to 101-84 victory over Philippines  FIBA WWQ 2026: Gallant D'Tigress fall 77-60 to Korea  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"